You have entered a large kitchen. There is a delicious smell of baking. Around the walls are hung enormous metal pans and cooking utensils. In one corner is a large old-fashioned kitchen range giving out a great heat. The only way out is by the stone staircase.
You can see a cook.

> speak to cook

> speak to cook
She is sobbing bitterly but manages to speak. "I'm glad to see you. I'm desperately worried. The Drogos are having a croquet party, and I have to bake a special cake for their tea on the lawn. The trouble is they insist it must be at least 26cm high and I can't get it to rise properly."

"Will you help me please? "

> yes
You say "yes."

The cook cheers up a bit.

"You see those three jars of white powder labelled TOLT, FIMA and MUOT? Well, I have to put in the right amount of each ingredient to make the cake rise to 26cms. I'll try another cake now and you tell me how much of each to use."

"How many grams of TOLT?"
> 6
OK, that's 6 grams of TOLT.

"How many grams of FIMA? "
> 6
OK, that's 6 grams of FIMA.

"How many grams of MUOT? "
> 6
OK, that's 6 grams of MUOT.

The cook puts the mixture into the oven and after a few minutes takes out the cake. It has risen to a height of 26cms.

The cook tastes the cake and says "It's rather salty, but just the right size."

She then fumbles under the table and hands you a flour bag. "I found this yesterday. It is no use to me."

Free from the pressure of making the cake, she sits down and falls asleep immediately.
