> push bath

> push bath
You launch the bath into the river and clamber in just as it leaves the bank.

Soon, however, water starts to come over the side and you have to return. The bath won't carry much weight. You must take fewer things with you or you will sink.

A large ape lumbers up to you and asks "Are you trying to get the ladder across the river? "

> yes
You say "yes."

"I would like to help you but I am a rather stupid ape...now if I were a wise animal like an owl, then I might be able to help you...perhaps you can turn me into an owl? "

"I once turned a pig into a sty. Would you like to know how I did it? " asks the ape.

> yes
You say "yes."

"Well," says the ape, "I did it bit by bit like this
  PIG
  BIG
  BAG
  SAG
  SAY
  STY
...It was very difficult. But you are much cleverer than I am so perhaps you can change me into an owl? "

The ape climbs a nearby tree and sits on a branch, waiting for you to start.
APE: "Now what's next?" asks the ape.
> awe
AWE: "OK," says the ape.
> owe
OWE: "OK," says the ape.
> owl
OWL: "That's it! " says the ape.

The ape immediately starts to sprout feathers. In less than a minute he has turned into a magnificant brown owl. He flaps his wings, a little uncertainly at first, and then swoops down. With his talons, he snatches the rope ladder, flies off with it towards the palace and soon disappears out of sight behind some trees.
